  "text": "The XPCOM component implementation follows Firefox's established patterns from the XPCOM subsystem and toolkit components. The implementation uses NS_DECL_ISUPPORTS macro from xpcom/base/nsISupportsImpl.h to declare reference counting support (QueryInterface, AddRef, Release methods). The NS_IMPL_ISUPPORTS macro from the same file generates the implementation of these methods.\n\nThe observer service interface is declared using NS_DECL_NSIOBSERVERSERVICE macro, found in xpcom/ds/nsObserverService.h. This macro generates method declarations for the nsIObserverService interface methods: AddObserver, RemoveObserver, NotifyObservers, HasObservers, and EnumerateObservers, as defined in xpcom/ds/nsIObserverService.idl.\n\nThe component registration uses NS_GENERIC_FACTORY_CONSTRUCTOR_INIT from xpcom/components/ModuleUtils.h, which generates a constructor function that instantiates the component and calls its Initialize method before QueryInterface. This pattern matches the usage seen in netwerk/build/nsNetModule.cpp.\n\nReference counting is implemented through macros that expand to inline implementations of AddRef and Release, using atomic operations and returning reference count values. The QueryInterface method is generated by the macros to support type casting between interfaces.\n\nThe implementation follows the pattern seen in toolkit/components/places/Database.h and Database.cpp, which also uses NS_DECL_NSIOBSERVER for observer interface declaration and NS_IMPL_ISUPPORTS for implementation. The component uses nsCOMPtr (referenced in nsISupportsUtils.h) for safe COM pointer management.\n\nShutdown handling follows Firefox conventions seen in nsObserverService.cpp, with a mIsShuttingDown flag to prevent use after shutdown. The component delegates to the system observer service obtained via mozilla::services::GetObserverService(), maintaining proper encapsulation and lifetime management consistent with Firefox's architecture."
}

